on:** Following the introduction of the company\'s three operating segments (Space, Connectivity, and AI) and the timeline of the Mergers.\n* **Common-Control Accounting, Retrospective Combination & Elimination of Transactions:**\n  > *"The Mergers have been accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control as Mr. Elon Musk had a controlling financial interest in the Company, xAI and X through his majority voting interest in each such entity during the periods presented in these consolidated financial statements. The Company’s consolidated financial statements have been prepared to reflect the retrospective combination of the net assets of the entities at their historical carrying amounts for all periods presented. No new goodwill or other intangible assets have been recorded and all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation."*\n* **Change in Reporting Entity:**\n  > *"The capital stock and shareholders’ equity for all periods presented reflects a continuation of the historical SpaceX capital stock and shareholders’ equity, combined with the historical capital stock and shareholders’ equity of X and xAI merged under common control... This presentation constitutes a change in reporting entity."*\n\n### 3. Note 2 - Summary of Significant Accounting Policies\n**Location:** Immediately following the merger accounting explanations and the justification for omitting separate financial statements for xAI and X.\n* **Elimination of Intercompany Transactions:**\n  > *"The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of the Company and its wholly owned subsidiaries. All intercompany balances and transactions have been eliminated in consolidation."*\n\n### 4. Related Party Transactions (Elon Musk & Affiliated Entities)\n**Location:** The section detailing commercial, licensing, and support agreements between the consolidated entities (SpaceX, xAI, X) and Tesla/The Boring Company. \n* **Context for