        output='Based on the provided text, here are the details regarding the Valor Equity Partners lease agreements, failed sale-leaseback transactions, and aggregate payment obligations:\n\n### **1. Lease Agreements**\nCertain subsidiaries of xAI (including CTC) have entered into equipment lease, sublease, and access agreements with Valor Equity Partners ("Valor"), an entity affiliated with board member Antonio J. Gracias. These include:\n*   **Three Computing Equipment Leases:** Agreements where an xAI subsidiary leases computing and related equipment from Valor. The lessees\' payments and performance obligations under these agreements are guaranteed by Space Exploration Technologies Corp. (SpaceX) or one of its subsidiaries.\n*   **"Valor transaction" (October 2025):** An equipment lease agreement entered into by CTC (amended on November 10, 2025) for certain AI infrastructure hardware.\n*   **"Valor transaction II" (January 2026):** A subsequent equipment lease agreement entered into by CTC (amended on February 18, 2026) for additional AI infrastructure hardware. \n\n### **2. Failed Sale-Leaseback Transactions**\nThe AI infrastructure hardware leases (Valor transaction and Valor transaction II) were deemed **failed sale-leaseback transactions** for accounting purposes, resulting in the company recording them as debt rather than standard operating/finance leases:\n*   **As of December 31, 2025:** Following the initial Valor transaction, the Company recorded related debt of **$455 million** (current) and **$4,052 million** (non-current) on the consolidated balance sheets, alongside $66 million in Interest expense for the year.\n*   **As of March 31, 2026:** Following both the November 2025 and January 2026 transactions, the combined related debt for these failed sale-leaseback transactions grew to **$1,121 million** (current) and **$7,920 million** (non-current). The Company also recorded $186 million in Interest expense for the three months ended March 31, 2026, related to these equipment lease agreements.\n\n### **3. Aggregate Payment Obligations**\nThe three primary computing equipment lease agreements carry massive aggregate cash payment obligations over the life of the leases:\n*   **First equipment lease:** **$6,986 million**\n*   **Second equipment lease:** **$6,633 million**\n*   **Third equipment lease:** **$6,587 million**\n\n*Note on Payments Made:* Pursuant to these lease agreements, the subsidiaries had already made cash payments of **$885 million in 2025**, and **$857 million** from January 1, 2026, through February 28, 2026. Additionally, X received minor API service payments from Valor ($1 million in 2024, $1 million in 2025, and $0.1 million in early 2026).',
