\n- **Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC** advised SpaceX on the xAI acquisition.\n- Affiliates of Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, BofA, Citigroup, J.P. Morgan, Barclays, Deutsche Bank, RBC, UBS, and Wells Fargo serve as lenders or agents under both the **SpaceX Bridge Loan** and the **SpaceX Credit Facility**.\n- A **Directed Share Program** reserves IPO shares for employees, management, business partners, and friends/family of management, exempt from standard lock-up restrictions.\n\n---\n\n## Pre-Merger Intercompany Activity: Where the Filing Discusses It\n\nThe filing **does not disclose specific details, amounts, or business descriptions of pre-merger intercompany transactions** between SpaceX, xAI, and X Holdings. Instead, it addresses their elimination in the following locations:\n\n### Location 1: Prospectus Preamble / Summary Historical Financial Data\nThe preamble states:\n> *"The consolidated financial statements of SpaceX have been retrospectively recast for all periods presented to include (i) the historical results of X.AI Holdings Corp., which was acquired by SpaceX, effective February 2, 2026 (the \'xAI Merger\'), and X Holdings Corp. (\'X Holdings\'), which was acquired by xAI, effective March 28, 2025 (the \'X Merger\'), because these transactions were between entities under common control..."*\n\n### Location 2: Note 1 — Nature of Business (Consolidated Financial Statements)\nThis is the most explicit discussion. The filing states:\n> *"The Mergers have been accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control as Mr. Elon Musk had a controlling financial interest in the Company, xAI and X through his majority voting interest in each such entity during the periods presented in these consolidated financial statements. The Company\'s consolidated financial statements have been prepared to reflect the retrospective combination of the net assets of the entities at their historical carrying amounts for all periods presented. No new goodwill or other intangible assets have been recorded and **all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation**."*\n\nThe note further clarifies that this presentation constitutes a **change in reporting entity**, with capital stock and shareholders\' equity for all periods reflecting a continuation of historical SpaceX equity combined with X and xAI equity, adjusted by the respective exchange ratios.\n\n### Location 3: Note 2 — Summary of Significant Accounting Policies\nThe standard consolidation policy states:\n> *"The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of the Company and its wholly owned subsidiaries. All intercompany balances and transactions have been eliminated in consolidation."*\n\n### Key Analytical Takeaway\n\nBecause the mergers were common-control reorganizations (not arm\'s-length acquisitions), **all pre-merger transactions between SpaceX, xAI, and X Holdings were eliminated** in the retrospectively recast financial statements. The filing does not break out or quantify what those internal transactions were — only that they have been fully eliminated. Consequently, no period in the financial statements reflects standalone SpaceX operations; every historical period presents the combined entity as if the three companies had always been consolidated. This is analytically material because it means investors cannot isolate SpaceX\'s pre-merger standalone financial performance from the S-1.\n\n---\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (Filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}',
